      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml] </span><strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and the <strong>remaining chopped ginger </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat, add the <strong>carrot</strong> <strong>ribbons</strong> and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving – this is your <strong>ginger & carrot rice</strong></p>",
